description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As a constantly evolving service, Intermediate Care continually reviews it’s service delivery to ensure the correct services are available for our patients. As such we are now looking for a full time Band 6 Occupational Therapist to join our therapy team on the community inpatient ward at Farnham Hospital for an initial six months fixed term contract with a view to becoming substantive. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Due to the growing demand for rehabilitation and optimisation back into the community, you will have specialist skills in timely assessment, treatment planning and rehabilitation, equipment provision and discharge planning, working with patients to enable them to regain their function through inpatient rehabilitation and onward referral to further maximise function once discharged.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As well as a diverse clinical role, this post will enable you to use your broader OT skills including direct management of junior staff and students. You will excel at MDT working and be keen to undertake service improvement projects to develop this role, and the team, further.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The service operates 8am-8pm 7 days a week and you will be expected to work on a rota basis to cover these hours. You must be able to travel independently for work purposes and have business insurance. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information please call Liam Poupart or Lisa Beadle on 01252 813847.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Liam Poupart&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Physio team lead&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;liam.poupart@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;01252 813847&lt;/p&gt;
